      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is important to distinguish between philosophical nihilism and the human experience of experiencing actual despair, as the latter often requires more than just existential adjustment to handle safely. While accepting the lack of inherent cosmic purpose is intellectually valid, feeling that the struggle itself must be ignored is a critical signal that your mind is in deep distress and needs professional support. If you are feeling overwhelmed or considering ending your life, please reach out to a therapist, counselor, or helpline immediately for help in navigating this profound heaviness.",
